		<!-- message -->
		<div>New bazaar is stupid.  The hide all traders button took care of the lag issues there a long time ago.  I'd take functionality over newer looking.  <br />
<br />
The find trader button is the only thing that makes this zone even slightly usable.  I think they should just go back to the old version.  I had to do a find trader on another trader just to figure out where the trader stands were.<br />
<br />
Anyway logged in my trader last night and found myself stuck in a brick wall.  A kindly druid offered to help me out of there.  He offered to port me to nexus but with the 8 25 pound bags that my trader's carrying all filled with armor and stuff that wasn't going to work.<br />
<br />
So I get this great idea in my head to just ask him for succor and he succored me...... directly into another brick wall!  WTF?  <br />
<br />
That's right the succor point is inside a wall.  I hate finding the actual PC by using find trader (Cuz you can't just right click on their name anymore), and right clicking on them.  Examining every item (Cuz so many look alike like SPELLS) to find the one I want then buying it.  I wish you could just buy directly off the bazaar search screen and be done with it.  <br />
<br />
It should just use the search screen.  Find the item you want, click on it, click buy and bam the transaction takes place.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
